The paper focuses on technical and security-related barriers to cloud adoption, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses data privacy and portability, which could also place it in the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category. The study also involves analyzing data and logistic regression, indicating that it could fit into the cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with cloud computing, which could place it in the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category.
